  <h1>The Last Trip</h1><div>
<br>Our last hike out was about four and a half miles with 3000 feet of elevation gain, so it was going to be a bit of a long day.&nbsp; Carrie has long maintained that hiking up is much nicer than hiking down, which I have come to agree is true.&nbsp; It's more of a workout, but much easier on the knees, balance, and brain (you don't have to watch where you're walking so as to avoid tumbling grandly down the canyon quite as much).&nbsp; We wanted to get an earlier start and got up with the sun to make coffee and start hiking before the heat of the day.<br><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi8zYmEwY2MxZi1jYmM3LTQzZTYtYTViOS1iMjYxZmEwMjcwZDI_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--7d9809851c5db800f6e8cd3eed11e20081d69ceb" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWt6WW1Fd1kyTXhaaTFqWW1NM0xUUXpaVFl0WVRWaU9TMWlNall4Wm1Fd01qY3daRElHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--5c9162a2d70ffe32108e7565b60f8577302dd201/IMG_7645.jpeg" filename="IMG_7645.jpeg" filesize="191874" width="640" height="853" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="making oats"><figure class="attachment attachment--preview attachment--jpeg">
